The 'most recent season' refers to the season with the highest year value in the seasons table; 
The 'win/loss records' include the number of wins and losses for each team; 
The 'winning percentages' are calculated based on the number of wins and losses; 
The 'points' refer to the total points earned by each team; 
The 'current streaks' refer to the current win or loss streak for each team.

sql:
SELECT SUM(home_wins) 
FROM season_stats 
WHERE team_id = (SELECT team_id FROM teams WHERE team_name = 'San Antonio Spurs');
